# Component Architecture

The components in this project follow a hierarchical organization:

## Component Types

- **UI Components**: [src/components/ui](mdc:src/components/ui)
  - Primitive UI components built on Radix UI
  - Examples: [Button](mdc:src/components/ui/button.tsx), [Card](mdc:src/components/ui/card.tsx)

- **Feature Components**: [src/components](mdc:src/components)
  - Higher-level components composed of UI primitives
  - Examples: [LoginForm](mdc:src/components/login-form.tsx), [AppSidebar](mdc:src/components/app-sidebar.tsx)

- **Page Components**: [src/app](mdc:src/app)
  - Route-specific components in the App Router structure

## Component Patterns

- Components use React Hook Form with Zod validation for forms
- UI components use class-variance-authority for variant management
- Components follow a composition pattern with clear separation of concerns
- Tailwind CSS is used for styling with utility classes

## Key Components

- [LoginForm](mdc:src/components/login-form.tsx): Authentication form
- [AppSidebar](mdc:src/components/app-sidebar.tsx): Main navigation sidebar
- [NavUser](mdc:src/components/nav-user.tsx): User navigation component
